## What Is This?

ECS Fargate does not have the same `imagePullPolicy` concept as Kubernetes, but the equivalent risk exists through how task definitions reference images. When an ECS task definition references an image by mutable tag (e.g., `webapp:latest`) rather than digest, every task launch re-resolves the tag — which may now point to a different image than when the task was last deployed.

Combined with mutable ECR tags (Lab 13), this means: tag gets silently overwritten, next ECS service scaling event or task restart pulls the new image, compromised version runs in production with no explicit deployment event.

---

## Vulnerable ECS Task Definition

```json
{
  "family": "webapp",
  "containerDefinitions": [{
    "name": "webapp",
    "image": "123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/webapp:latest",
    "portMappings": [{"containerPort": 8080}]
  }]
}
```

Problems:
- References `:latest` — mutable tag
- No digest pin — image can change between task launches
- No way to detect if the image changed between deployments

---

## Detection

```bash
# Find all ECS task definitions using tag-based image references
aws ecs list-task-definitions --status ACTIVE \
    --query 'taskDefinitionArns[]' --output text | \
    tr '\t' '\n' | while read arn; do
        aws ecs describe-task-definition --task-definition "$arn" \
            --query 'taskDefinition.containerDefinitions[].image' \
            --output text | tr '\t' '\n' | while read img; do
                if ! echo "$img" | grep -q '@sha256:'; then
                    echo "TAG REFERENCE: $arn -> $img"
                fi
            done
    done

# Simulated output:
# TAG REFERENCE: arn:aws:ecs:us-east-1:123456789012:task-definition/webapp:42
#   -> 123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/webapp:latest
```

---

## Fix — Always Deploy by Digest

```groovy
// Jenkins pipeline — capture digest after push, deploy by digest
stage('Build and Push') {
    steps {
        script {
            sh "docker build -t ${IMAGE_NAME}:${BUILD_NUMBER} ."
            sh """
                aws ecr get-login-password --region ${AWS_REGION} \
                    | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin ${ECR_REGISTRY}
                docker push ${IMAGE_NAME}:${BUILD_NUMBER}
            """
            // Capture the digest immediately after push
            env.IMAGE_DIGEST = sh(
                script: """
                    aws ecr describe-images \
                        --repository-name ${ECR_REPO} \
                        --image-ids imageTag=${BUILD_NUMBER} \
                        --query 'imageDetails[0].imageDigest' \
                        --output text
                """,
                returnStdout: true
            ).trim()
            echo "Image digest: ${IMAGE_DIGEST}"
        }
    }
}

stage('Deploy to ECS') {
    steps {
        script {
            // Register new task definition with digest reference
            def taskDefJson = """
            {
                "family": "${ECS_TASK_FAMILY}",
                "containerDefinitions": [{
                    "name": "webapp",
                    "image": "${IMAGE_NAME}@${IMAGE_DIGEST}",
                    "portMappings": [{"containerPort": 8080}],
                    "essential": true
                }],
                "requiresCompatibilities": ["FARGATE"],
                "networkMode": "awsvpc",
                "cpu": "256",
                "memory": "512"
            }
            """
            // Deploy using digest — immutable reference
            sh """
                aws ecs register-task-definition \
                    --cli-input-json '${taskDefJson}'

                aws ecs update-service \
                    --cluster ${ECS_CLUSTER} \
                    --service ${ECS_SERVICE} \
                    --task-definition ${ECS_TASK_FAMILY}
            """
        }
    }
}
```

### Fixed Task Definition

```json
{
  "family": "webapp",
  "containerDefinitions": [{
    "name": "webapp",
    "image": "123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/webapp@sha256:53f02d32...",
    "portMappings": [{"containerPort": 8080}]
  }]
}
```

The digest reference is immutable. Even if the tag is overwritten in ECR, this task definition always pulls exactly the image that was deployed.

